  "learn": {
    "heading": "What is a unit rate?",
    "intro": "<p>The word <strong>\"per\"</strong> means <em>for each one</em>. A <strong>unit rate</strong> is the amount for exactly <strong>1</strong>. To find it, <strong>divide</strong> by how many groups there are.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>$6 for 3 pens</strong> → 6 ÷ 3 = <strong>$2 per pen</strong> (the cost for ONE pen).",
      "<strong>40 miles in 2 hours</strong> → 40 ÷ 2 = <strong>20 miles per hour</strong> (distance in ONE hour)."
    ]
  },
